{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782031725,"nonce":"DLCCBq1IJkRQ9aqdLLCfjPo6nro=","title":"**Summary**","message":"When a query uses `.distinct()`, SQL requires every `ORDER BY` expression to also\nappear in the projection. Today this is only enforced by the database at execution\ntime; model it at compile time.\n\n**Motivation**\n`db.from::\u003cT\u003e().distinct().order_by(|(u,)| u.id.asc()).select(|(u,)| u.name)` renders\n`SELECT DISTINCT name ... ORDER BY id`, which PostgreSQL rejects (\"for SELECT\nDISTINCT, ORDER BY expressions must appear in select list\"). The `distinct()` builder\nadvertises composing with ordering, so the unsupported subset should be caught at\nbuild time rather than failing at runtime. (Documented as a known limitation in the\n`distinct()` rustdoc for now.)\n\n**Scope**\n- v1: when DISTINCT is set, require each accumulated `ORDER BY` key to be present in\n  the final projection (by column/expr identity).\n- Out of scope: arbitrary expression-equality between order keys and projected\n  expressions beyond column identity.\n\n**Plan**\n- The order keys are carried in the `OrderBy` chain nodes (kind `K`); the projection\n  is known at `.select()`. Thread a type-level set of order-key identities and, when\n  `Distinct` is in the chain, constrain at `select` that each is a member of the\n  projection's column/kind set. Mirror the existing aggregate/GROUP-BY type-level\n  validation machinery (`NonAggregateAst`, projection classification).\n- Likely a dedicated trait relating order-key marker types to the projection tuple,\n  gated on the presence of `Distinct` in the base chain.\n\n**Files**\ncrates/squealy/src/query.rs (Distinct, OrderBy, select bounds), expr.rs (order-key\nidentity), + compile-fail tests.\n\n**Tests**\n- compile-fail: distinct().order_by(unselected).select(...).\n- pass: distinct().order_by(selected).select(...).\n\n**Size**\nMedium-large (type-level set membership relating order keys to projection).\n\n**Acceptance**\nOrdering a distinct query by an unselected column fails to compile; ordering by a\nselected column still works; existing tests green.","files":null}]}